Bayesian Correlayed t-test

bayesianCorrelatedT.test.Rd

This function performs the Bayesian correlated t-test

bayesianCorrelatedT.test(x, y = NULL, rho = 1/length(x),
  rope.min = -0.01, rope.max = 0.01)

Arguments

x

First vector of observations
y

Second vector of observations
rho

Expectated correlation.
rope.min

Lower limit of the rope considered
rope.max

Upper limit of the rope considered

Value

List with probabilities for each region and a sample of posterior distribution.

Examples

bayesianCorrelatedT.test(results.rf[1, ], results.knn[1, ])
